task_description:
Analyze the following code and determine its time complexity in Big O notation:

def find_max(arr):
    max_val = arr[0]
    for i in range(1, len(arr)):
        if arr[i] > max_val:
            max_val = arr[i]
    return max_val

Analyze and suggest optimizations for this code:

def find_duplicates(arr):
    duplicates = []
    for i in range(len(arr)):
        for j in range(i+1, len(arr)):
            if arr[i] == arr[j] and arr[i] not in duplicates:
                duplicates.append(arr[i])
    return duplicates

Explain how this recursive function works and trace its execution for factorial(5):

def factorial(n):
    if n <= 1:
        return 1
    return n * factorial(n - 1)
